This paper deals with learning and inference in relational Markov random fields, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the use of loopy belief propagation, which is a common technique in probabilistic graphical models and inference algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DB (Databases). The paper also deals with large networks and complex domains, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
